[TILE:digital-twins-001]
title: "Digital twin architectures and sensor fusion — Core Principles"
tags: [domain:digital-twins, type:reference, tier:foundation]
body: |-
  # Digital twin architectures and sensor fusion
  
  ## Core Principles
  
  1. **Principle One** — Every signal carries uncertainty. The measure of a good system is not how well it handles perfect inputs, but how gracefully it degrades under noise.
  
  2. **Principle Two** — The most elegant solution in simulation is often the least practical in the field. Benchmark on real hardware, not synthetic traces.
  
  3. **Principle Three** — Information decays with distance. Compensate at the source, not the receiver.
  
  These principles drive every design decision in this domain. When in doubt, optimize for the worst case.

[TILE:digital-twins-002]
title: "Digital twin architectures and sensor fusion — Key Metrics"
tags: [domain:digital-twins, type:reference, tier:foundation]
body: |-
  # Key Metrics

  | Metric | Target | Warning | Critical |
  |--------|--------|---------|----------|
  | Latency | < 10ms | 10-50ms | > 50ms |
  | Throughput | > 1000 Hz | 100-1000 Hz | < 100 Hz |
  | Accuracy | > 95% | 85-95% | < 85% |
  | Power | < 10W | 10-30W | > 30W |
  
  These are deployment-specific. Adjust per hardware target.

[TILE:digital-twins-003]
title: "Digital twin architectures and sensor fusion — Common Pitfalls"
tags: [domain:digital-twins, type:pattern, tier:implementation]
body: |-
  # Common Pitfalls

  1. **Premature Optimization** — Optimizing before profiling is the #1 source of wasted engineering time.
  2. **Over-fitting to Test Data** — If validation accuracy is suspiciously high, check for data leakage.
  3. **Ignoring the Tail Latency** — P50 might be 1ms, but P99 is 500ms. The tail kills user experience.
  4. **Hardcoding Constants** — Wavelengths, thresholds, and margins change. Make them configurable.
  5. **Synthetic-Only Testing** — If it hasn't run on real hardware with real data, it doesn't work.

[TILE:digital-twins-004]
title: "Digital twin architectures and sensor fusion — Design Patterns"
tags: [domain:digital-twins, type:pattern, tier:architecture]
body: |-
  # Design Patterns

  ## Pattern: Pipeline Decomposition
  Break the problem into stages with clearly defined interfaces between them.
  
  ## Pattern: Observer-Consensus
  Multiple observers each produce a hypothesis. A consensus layer merges them.
  
  ## Pattern: Graceful Degradation
  When a component fails, the system degrades predictably rather than crashing.

[TILE:digital-twins-005]
title: "Digital twin architectures and sensor fusion — Hardware Considerations"
tags: [domain:digital-twins, type:reference, tier:tradeoffs]
body: |-
  # Hardware Considerations

  | Component | Preferred | Acceptable | Avoid |
  |-----------|-----------|------------|-------|
  | Compute | GPU with tensor cores | CPU with SIMD | Microcontroller |
  | Memory | Unified memory | Discrete GPU RAM | Shared system RAM |
  | Storage | NVMe SSD | SATA SSD | HDD |
  | Network | 10GbE | 1GbE | WiFi |

[TILE:digital-twins-006]
title: "Digital twin architectures and sensor fusion — Testing Strategy"
tags: [domain:digital-twins, type:pattern, tier:testing]
body: |-
  # Testing Strategy

  ## Levels
  1. **Unit** — Test each component in isolation
  2. **Integration** — Test component interfaces
  3. **End-to-End** — Test the full pipeline
  4. **Stress** — Test under worst-case load
  5. **Regression** — Continuous verification

  ## Key Assertions
  - Output bounds are within expected ranges
  - Performance meets latency/throughput targets
  - Memory usage stays within budget

[TILE:digital-twins-007]
title: "Digital twin architectures and sensor fusion — Deployment Checklist"
tags: [domain:digital-twins, type:checklist, tier:operations]
body: |-
  # Deployment Checklist

  - [ ] All unit tests pass
  - [ ] Integration tests pass on target hardware
  - [ ] Latency meets target (measured on-device)
  - [ ] Memory usage within budget
  - [ ] Logging configured
  - [ ] Monitoring configured
  - [ ] Rollback plan documented
  - [ ] Contact on-call engineer notified

[TILE:digital-twins-008]
title: "Digital twin architectures and sensor fusion — Optimization Guide"
tags: [domain:digital-twins, type:guide, tier:implementation]
body: |-
  # Optimization Guide

  ## Order of Operations
  1. Profile first
  2. Fix the worst bottleneck
  3. Re-profile
  4. Repeat
  
  ## Common Optimizations
  - Fuse kernels where possible
  - Reduce memory transfers
  - Use mixed precision
  - Batch operations
  - Pre-compute constants

[TILE:digital-twins-009]
title: "Digital twin architectures and sensor fusion — Safety Margins"
tags: [domain:digital-twins, type:reference, tier:operations]
body: |-
  # Safety Margins

  | Resource | Budget | Buffer | Hard Limit |
  |----------|--------|--------|------------|
  | CPU | 70% | 20% | 90% |
  | Memory | 60% | 25% | 85% |
  | GPU | 75% | 15% | 90% |
  | Power | 80% | 10% | 90% |
  | Bandwidth | 50% | 30% | 80% |

